# MovieHub AI Development Guide (AGENTS.md)

## Project Overview

MovieHub is a production-ready Telegram Movie Storage & Distribution Bot built with Python.

The bot stores movie files in Telegram Database Channels while storing all metadata in MongoDB Atlas.

The bot is designed to run 24/7 on Android using Termux and must be lightweight, modular, maintainable, and fully configurable from inside Telegram without editing source code.

The only values that may exist in `.env` are startup secrets such as Bot Token, MongoDB URI, and API credentials required to bootstrap the application.

Everything else must be stored in MongoDB and editable from the Telegram Admin Panel.

---

## Tech Stack

* Python 3.12+
* Pyrogram
* Motor (MongoDB)
* MongoDB Atlas
* FastAPI (Redirect Server)
* Uvicorn
* Pydantic
* AsyncIO
* Telegram Database Channels

---

## Core Principles

* Async-first architecture.
* Modular codebase.
* Small focused modules.
* No duplicate logic.
* Clear separation of responsibilities.
* Type hints throughout.
* Comprehensive logging.
* Proper exception handling.
* Production-ready code only.

---

## Development Rules

Always implement one feature at a time.

Do not generate placeholder implementations.

Do not hardcode configuration values.

Avoid global state whenever possible.

Prefer dependency injection and service classes.

Each feature must be testable independently.

Never rewrite unrelated files.

When modifying existing code, preserve backward compatibility whenever possible.

---

## Project Structure

The project should be organized into modules for:

* Bot
* Handlers
* Keyboards
* Database
* Models
* Services
* Utilities
* Configuration
* Redirect Server
* Tests
* Scripts

Keep responsibilities separated.

---

## Configuration

All editable configuration must come from MongoDB.

Examples include:

* Bot Name
* Welcome Message
* About Message
* Channels
* Force Subscribe
* Auto Delete Timer
* Warning Messages
* Button Text
* Auto Post Template
* Latest Movie Count

The bot should not require restarting when configuration changes.

---

## User Interface

The UI should be modern, clean, emoji-friendly, and easy to navigate using inline buttons.

Avoid commands wherever possible.

---

## Admin Panel

The Admin Panel should be completely button-based.

Every workflow should guide the administrator step by step.

---

## Coding Style

* Use descriptive names.
* Prefer composition over inheritance.
* Keep functions short.
* Keep classes focused.
* Avoid deeply nested code.
* Write reusable utilities.

---

## AI Workflow

Before implementing a feature:

1. Understand the requirement.
2. Explain the implementation plan briefly.
3. Generate production-ready code.
4. Explain what changed.
5. Mention any manual testing steps.

---

## Goal

The objective is to build a maintainable, scalable, production-quality Telegram application suitable for long-term development.
